snippet: The influence of China hung over the deliberations at the meeting of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations, which Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton attended.
abstract: Association of Southeast Asian Nations, meeting in Cambodia, a close ally of China, are unlikely to reach any accord as the host country refuses to play the customary role of seeking agreement over disputes among the 10 participating countries and China over the South China Sea.
lead_paragraph: The influence of China hung over the deliberations at the meeting of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations, which Secretary of State Hillary Rodham Clinton attended.

headline.seo: Asian Leaders Fail to Resolve Disputes on South China Sea
headline.main: Asian Leaders at Regional Meeting Fail to Resolve Disputes Over South China Sea
headline.print_headline: Asian Leaders at Regional Meeting Fail to Resolve Disputes Over South China Sea
